paragraphs.title: Show current tables and Count
paragraphs.text:
from pyspark.sql import Row 
tables = [Row(table=tableName, count=sqlContext.table(tableName).count()) for tableName, isTemp in sqlContext.tables().collect() if isTemp==False]
sqlContext.createDataFrame(tables).registerTempTable("table_info")

paragraphs.title: Show Count of ratings of The Movies
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT m.movieId, m.title, count(r.rating) as count
FROM ml_movies m, ml_ratings r
WHERE m.movieId = r.movieId
GROUP BY m.movieId, m.title
ORDER BY count(r.rating) DESC

paragraphs.title: Show Avg Of Ratings Of The Movies
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT m.movieId, m.title, avg(r.rating) as avg
FROM ml_movies m, ml_ratings r
WHERE m.movieId = r.movieId
GROUP BY m.movieId, m.title
ORDER BY avg(r.rating) DESC

paragraphs.title: Show the movies the user have seen
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT m.movieId, m.title, r.rating 
FROM ml_movies m, ml_ratings r
WHERE m.movieId = r.movieId and r.userId=${userId=1}

result.msg:
movieId	title	rating
169	Free Willy 2: The Adventure Home (1995)	2.5
2471	Crocodile Dundee II (1988)	3.0
48516	Departed, The (2006)	5.0

paragraphs.title: Show the rating of The Movie
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT m.movieId, m.title,r.userId, r.rating
FROM ml_movies m, ml_ratings r
WHERE m.movieId = r.movieId AND 
      m.movieId=${moveId=1}
ORDER BY r.rating DESC

paragraphs.title: Show The Count of The Genres
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT g.feature, Count(r.rating) as count
FROM ml_movies m, ml_ratings r, ml_movies_features g
WHERE m.movieId = r.movieId AND 
      m.movieId = g.movieId
GROUP BY g.feature
ORDER BY Count(r.rating) DESC

paragraphs.title: Show The AVG Of The Genres
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT g.feature, avg(r.rating) as avg
FROM ml_movies m, ml_ratings r, ml_movies_features g
WHERE m.movieId = r.movieId AND 
      m.movieId = g.movieId
GROUP BY g.feature
ORDER BY avg(r.rating) DESC
